  "prompt": "How can I know if I tongue thrust during my sleep?",
  "response": "To determine if you tongue thrust during sleep, you can:\n\n1. Look for Physical Signs:\n- Dental misalignment\n- Open bite\n- Flared front teeth\n- Difficulty closing lips completely\n\n2. Observe Morning Symptoms:\n- Sore or tired jaw muscles\n- Unusual tongue positioning when waking\n- Dry mouth\n\n3. Get Professional Assessment:\n- Consult a dentist or orthodontist\n- They can examine your teeth and bite alignment\n- May recommend specialized diagnostic tests\n\n4. Video or Audio Recording:\n- Record yourself sleeping\n- Look for visible tongue movements\n- Listen for unusual mouth sounds\n\n5. Use Sleep Monitoring Devices:\n- Some advanced sleep tracking apps/devices\n- Can potentially detect oral muscle movements\n\n6. Professional Sleep Study:\n- Most comprehensive evaluation\n- Can precisely document tongue movements during sleep\n\n7. Ask Sleep Partner:\n- They might notice tongue or mouth movements\n- Can provide additional observation insights\n\n8. Consult Orofacial Myologists:\n- Specialists who diagnose and treat tongue positioning issues\n\nConsulting healthcare professionals is the most accurate way to diagnose sleep-related tongue thrusting.",
